	<p>
    <div style="clear:both;"></div><h2>A World of Identity</h2>
<p><a href="http://www.windley.com/events/iiw2007a/register.shtml"><img title="IIW2007 Registration&#13;&#10;banner" alt="IIW2007 Registration banner" hspace="3" src="http://www.windley.com/events/iiw2007a/images/iiw2007sidebar-tall.png" align="left" vspace="3" border="0" /></a> No, Internet Identity is not some New Age self-discovery program.&nbsp; Well, I don&rsquo;t think so.&nbsp; Perhaps it helps to have done that first.</p>
<p>Now that I am securely registered for <a href="http://www.windley.com/events/iiw2007a/announcement.shtml">IIW2007a</a> as it is known to the cognoscenti, and I have my travel tickets, I&rsquo;m willing to share this event with you too.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/orcmid/tags/iiw2006/">IIW2006a was fabulous</a> and I am happy to be returning and seeing what&rsquo;s new.&nbsp; The progress of CardSpace (InfoCards) and OpenId portends some interesting activity in May.&nbsp; </p>
<p>For myself, I am closer to scratching an itch for adopting OpenId and Cards in a reference implementation that I have in mind.&nbsp; I should be ready for some serious envisioning by May.&nbsp; With luck, I might have something useful to offer as well.</p><div class="bjtags">Tags:  <a rel="tag" href="http://technorati.com/tag/orcmid">orcmid</a>, <a rel="tag" href="http://technorati.com/tag/IIW2007">IIW2007</a>, <a rel="tag" href="http://technorati.com/tag/Identity">Identity</a>, <a rel="tag" href="http://technorati.com/tag/OpenId">OpenId</a>, <a rel="tag" href="http://technorati.com/tag/CardSpace">CardSpace</a></div><div style="clear:both; padding-bottom:0.25em"></div>
    </p>
